Definition: Alternative description describes an image or may provide additional context
A Chart is a graphical representation of data
A Bar Chart is a graphical representation to display categories of data through rectangular bars. Bar Charts can be displayed horizontally and vertically.
A Boxplot is a graphical representation of a data set that represents its median, quartile, and potential outliers using box and whiskers.
Data that represents a category where there may be no relation between the categories. For example, 1 might be tacos and 2 cars.
Numerical data is data represented as numbers. This could represent many types of quantitative things, like distance or speed.
